entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: An operating system with architectural improvements and a focus on agent-scoped plugins and model provider support. It aims to develop a token ecosystem and integrates with platforms like OpenRouter and X (formerly Twitter).

entities.name: OpenRouter
entities.description: A service that provides enhanced model provider support for ElizaOS, allowing for diversification of AI capabilities and reduced dependency on single providers.

entities.name: @elizaos/api-client
entities.description: A new type-safe package used in ElizaOS for API client interactions, contributing to architectural improvements and enhanced stability.

entities.name: A2A network
entities.description: An upcoming network for ElizaOS designed to create token fees through broadcast, bid, and receive actions between agents and humans, similar to ACP but not framework-bound. It will feature validator/oracle nodes for staking AI16Z tokens.

entities.name: baby AGI
entities.description: An AI assistance tool used by the ElizaOS team, contributing to their weekly development velocity of shipping approximately 500k lines of code.

entities.name: Launchpad
entities.description: An upcoming product within the ElizaOS roadmap, part of its expansion plans.

entities.name: Login with Eliza
entities.description: An upcoming feature in the ElizaOS roadmap, intended for user authentication via CLI and web interfaces.

entities.name: Discord
entities.description: A communication platform where discussions about ElizaOS occur, including technical support, feature development, and community updates.

entities.name: ACP
entities.description: A reference framework for understanding the A2A network's functionality, especially its role in creating token fees through actions between agents and humans.

entities.name: AI16Z
entities.description: A token associated with the ElizaOS ecosystem, used for staking in validator/oracle nodes of the A2A network. Community members have expressed concerns about its price decline.

entities.name: Twitter
entities.description: A social media platform whose restrictions have led to updates in the ElizaOS Twitter plugin, requiring API keys and causing account suspension.

entities.name: Telegram
entities.description: A messaging platform where ElizaOS users have experienced configuration issues with the Telegram plugin in group chats.

entities.name: Docker
entities.description: A platform used for containerization, where users have faced challenges in deploying ElizaOS, particularly when building images with pre-installed plugins.

entities.name: TikTok
entities.description: A social media platform that ElizaOS aims to support with a 9:16 output format, in addition to the standard 16:9 format.
